  <description>from a URL.</description>
  <command interpreter="bash">
    import_and_validate_ometiff.sh $image_name 
  </command>
  <inputs>
    <param name="image_name" type="text" value="https://downloads.openmicroscopy.org/images/OME-TIFF/2016-06/modulo/FLIM-ModuloAlongC.ome.tiff" label="Provide an image URL"/>
  </inputs>
  <outputs>
    <data format="tiff" name="image" from_work_dir="image.ome.tif"/>
  </outputs>
<help>

**Description**

Downloads an OME.TIFF from URL and validates the file using BioFormats_ command line tools_.

-----

**Input**

A link to an existing OME.TIFF (URL).

-----

**Output**

If the file is a valid OME.TIFF, then it is placed in the workspace of the current history. Returns false otherwise.

.. _BioFormats: http://www.openmicroscopy.org/site/products/bio-formats
.. _tools: http://www.openmicroscopy.org/site/support/bio-formats5.5/users/comlinetools

</help>
</tool>
